---
title: Sweet Chili & Soy-Glazed Meatballs over Ginger Ponzu Veggie Stir-Fry
description: One of our favorite cheffy tricks for taking meatballs from ordinary to extraordinary? Just add a flavorful glaze! Here, we blend scallions and ginger into ground beef, then form into meatballs and roast until tender. While they’re still hot from the oven, we toss them in a blend of soy glaze and chili sauce for spicy, sweet, and savory notes. They’re served over a stir-fry of tender bell pepper, carrots, green beans, and citrusy ponzu sauce, then sprinkled with sesame seeds for nutty crunch.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/sweet-chili-soy-glazed-meatballs-a5f76971.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sweet-chili-soy-glazed-meatballs-5ffca6445307755d3768ed26-a7ac078e.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-chili-soy-glazed-meatballs-5ffca6445307755d3768ed26
cuisine: Asian
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 640 kcal
  fat: 33 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 55 g
  sugar: 32 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1830 mg
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens; mince
whites. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim @green beans{6%ounce}
if necessary. Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1} into strips.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup},
scallion whites, half the ginger, @salt{3/4%tsp}, and @pepper{}.

Form mixture into 10-12 (20-24 for 4) 1 1/2-inch meatballs. Spread out on a
#baking sheet{}.

Bake on top rack until meatballs are browned and cooked through, ~{14-16%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add green beans and bell pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until
browned and tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @shredded carrots{4%ounce}; cook, stirring, until slightly softened,
~{1-2%minutes}. Season generously with salt and pepper.

Add @ponzu sauce{12%milliliters}, half the @sesame seeds{1/2%tablespoon} (save
the rest for serving), remaining ginger, and @butter{1%tablespoon} to pan with
veggies.

Cook, stirring, until ginger is fragrant and butter has melted, ~{1%minute}.
Season with salt and pepper.

Remove pan from heat; keep covered.

In a second #large microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}
with @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}; microwave until just warmed through,
~{30%seconds}.

Once meatballs are fully cooked, carefully add to #bowl{} and toss with sauce
to coat.

Divide veggie stir-fry between plates or shallow bowls; top with meatballs and
any remaining sauce. Sprinkle with scallion greens and remaining
@sesame seeds{1/2%tablespoon}. Serve.